Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

**1. Override `OnBackButtonPressed` and add a custom toolbar item:**

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();

        // Hide default back button, add custom "Cancel" button
        Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior(this, new BackButtonBehavior
        {
            TextOverride = "Cancel",
            Command = new Command(async () => await TryNavigateBack())
        });
    }

    // Intercept hardware/gesture back navigation
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Fire-and-forget the async confirmation
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () => await TryNavigateBack());
            return true; // Cancel the default navigation
        }

        return base.OnBackButtonPressed(); // Allow navigation
    }

    private async Task TryNavigateBack()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave)
                return; // User chose to stay
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoBackAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- `OnBackButtonPressed` handles Android hardware back and gestures — return `true` to cancel navigation.
- `Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior` customizes the toolbar back button (text, icon, or command).
- On iOS, the swipe-back gesture isn't caught by `OnBackButtonPressed`. To block it, you can also set `IsEnabled = false` on the `BackButtonBehavior` conditionally, or disable the gesture via a platform-specific renderer.

**Optional — disable iOS swipe-back while dirty:**

```csharp
#if IOS
protected override void OnAppearing()
{
    base.OnAppearing();
    // Disable interactivePopGesture when there are unsaved changes
    var nav = Platform.GetCurrentUIViewController()?.NavigationController;
    if (nav != null)
        nav.InteractivePopGestureRecognizer.Enabled = !_hasUnsavedChanges;
}
#endif
```
